Title: Crowd greeting Magic Johnson at Lakers NBA championship rally in Los Angeles, Calif., 1980

Caption: Text from the newspaper caption: Mr. and Mrs. George Lockwood Eastman, Jr., whose wedding took place Tuesday in St. Paul's Cathedral, are motoring to New York. They sail on the Majestic next Saturday with England and an Oxford Group House Party as their objective. They plan to return late in July to make their new home here. Mrs. Eastman is the former Louisa Forrester, daughter of Mrs. Frank L. Forrester. She is a member of the Los Angeles Junior League and was graduated from Vassar College.

Curious spectators who crowded about the swimmers while they were making their last-minute preparations held up the start of the race while the beach was being cleared...The number 72 beside Ross was the number carried by his observation boat, on board which were trainers, food and stimulants and an official observer. Title: Audience at Los Angeles Times' First Annual Fashion Show, Los Angeles Times building, 1935
Subject: Auditoriums $z California $z Los Angeles
Subject Name: Los Angeles Times Building (Los Angeles, Calif.)
Caption: Text from newspaper caption: Women Crowd Times Auditorium for Fall Fashion Show, Auditorium Taxed to Capacity As Women See Afternoon Parade of Models, Packed to capacity for three shows yesterday, The Times auditorium proved unequal to the crowds demanding admittance to the special fashion show and model parade of fall wearing apparel. Above photo shows crowd at the afternoon show at 2:30 o'clock, which was equaled by the crowd at 11 a.m. and at 5:30 p.m. Three shows are to follow Friday and at the same hours and the advance request for tickets indicates another day of capacity attendance. The show was planned for a single day but requests for admittance were so heavy that an extra three showings were added. ["Fall Styles Make Debut." Los Angeles Times, 11 Oct. 1935]

Title: Los Angeles River from the Main Street Bridge during rainstorm flooding, Los Angeles, 1927
Subject: Storms $z California $z Los Angeles
Caption: Text from newspaper caption: Thundering Waters Tear at Toppling Bridges. Tempest Turns River Into Destructive Force. Hungry flood waters of the raging Los Angeles River assailing the Main-street bridge. These waters rioting over an area which normally is an arroyo seco or dry river bed. A number of bridges have been swept out or badly damaged by the stream, transformed from an innocuous pygmy to a destructive giant almost overnight [Los Angeles Times, 17 Feb. 1927: 3].

Subject: City & town halls $z California $z Los Angeles
Subject Name: Los Angeles City Hall (Los Angeles, Calif.)

Caption: Text from newspaper caption: This isn't the Cat and the Canary, it's the Cat and the Linnet, but it's a real, hair-raising murder melodrama as you'll find in the last chapter. Title: Portrait of the five pilots who flew the bodies of Will Rogers and Wiley Post to Union Air Terminal, Burbank, 1935
Subject: Transportation
Caption: Text from newspaper caption: They Flew Plane Returning Illustrious Dead: These men flew the bodies of Will Rogers and Wiley Post into Union Air Terminal last night. Left to right they are William A. Winston, pilot; J. L. Fleming, junior pilot; T. W. Dowling, assistant superintendent of communications; Tom Ward, engineer, and Capt. Joe Crosson, hero-flyer, who brought the bodies out of Alaska. The plane also carried Col. Clarence M. Young, general manager of the Pacific Coast division of Pan American. (Los Angeles Times, "Bodies of Rogers and Post Arrive Here; "Mourning Throngs in Silent Tribute; Humorist to Lie in State Thursday; Public Memorial Rites in Bowl; Post's Remains to Be Sent to Home in East Today; Last Journey Told," 8/20/1935)

Title: Portrait of two of the pilots who flew the bodies of Will Rogers and Wiley Post to Union Air Terminal, Burbank, 1935
Subject: Transportation
Caption: Text from newspaper caption or a similar photograph: They Flew Plane Returning Illustrious Dead: These men flew the bodies of Will Rogers and Wiley Post into Union Air Terminal last night. Left to right they are William A. Winston, pilot; J. L. Fleming, junior pilot; T. W. Dowling, assistant superintendent of communications; Tom Ward, engineer, and Capt. Joe Crosson, hero-flyer, who brought the bodies out of Alaska. The plane also carried Col. Clarence M. Young, general manager of the Pacific Coast division of Pan American. (Los Angeles Times, "Bodies of Rogers and Post Arrive Here; "Mourning Throngs in Silent Tribute; Humorist to Lie in State Thursday; Public Memorial Rites in Bowl; Post's Remains to Be Sent to Home in East Today; Last Journey Told," 8/20/1935)

Title: Frances Pyle models a gown at the Times' First Annual Fashion Show, Los Angeles, 1935
Subject: Fashion models $z California $z Los Angeles
Subject Name: Los Angeles Times Building (Los Angeles, Calif.)
Caption: Text from newspaper caption of related photograph: Women Crowd Times Auditorium for Fall Fashion Show, Auditorium Taxed to Capacity As Women See Afternoon Parade of Models, Packed to capacity for three shows yesterday, The Times auditorium proved unequal to the crowds demanding admittance to the special fashion show and model parade of fall wearing apparel. Above photo shows crowd at the afternoon show at 2:30 o'clock, which was equaled by the crowd at 11 a.m. and at 5:30 p.m. Three shows are to follow Friday and at the same hours and the advance request for tickets indicates another day of capacity attendance. The show was planned for a single day but requests for admittance were so heavy that an extra three showings were added. ["Fall Styles Make Debut," Los Angeles Times, 11 Oct. 1935]

Title: "Wonder Woman" stuntwoman Kitty O'Neil leaping off Valley Hilton in Sherman Oaks, Calif., 1979
Subject: Wonder Woman (Television program)
Caption: It wasn't a plane. It wasn't a bird. It wasn't even Wonder Woman. It was a stunt. On Monday, stuntwoman Kitty O'Neil plunged 127 feet from atop the Valley Hilton in Sherman Oaks into an inflated air bag at the pool deck--as the scene was being filmed for an upcoming two-hour special episode of the Wonder Woman series. A Warner Brothers spokeswoman said Miss O'Neil, who is deaf, established a new high fall record and broke her own previous mark of 120 feet. Before the leap, Miss O'Neil practiced by making two 10-story jumps. After the leap, she rode to the airport for a return flight to Bonneville, Utah, where she's attempting to set a new world land speed record in her jet powered car.

Caption: INTERCHANGE DESIGNERS-Mrs. Marilyn Reece, left, stands by the three level Santa Monica-San Diego Freeway interchange she designed near Sepulveda and Olympic Blvds. With her is state highway engineer Mrs. Carol Schumaker who designed San Diego-San Gabriel River-Garden Grove complex.

Title: Mas Miyakoda, manager of Sumitomo Bank of California demonstrating how to use ATM machine in Monterey Park, Calif., 1969
Subject: Automated tellers--United States--1960-1970
Caption: INSTANT MONEY--Mas Miyakoda, manager of Sumitomo Bank of California's Monterey Park branch, shows how to work money machine. Specially coded credit card is inserted in slot, buttons at bottom are punched and cash is delivered to the customer.

Title: Los Angeles City Council chambers during debate on requiring Communists to register, Dorothy Healey at microphone, 1950
Subject: Communism--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: INSIDE-- This is a section of Council chambers showing the near-record crowd that listened to testimony.  While Los Angeles Communists jammed chambers, it was apparent that the anti-Reds were well represented.

Title: Airplane passing over a house being moved near Los Angeles International Airport, 1970
Subject: Airplanes--Landing
Caption: INCOMING AND OUTGOING--While a jetliner sweeps in low for a landing at International Airport, movers jack up another one of the houses being hauled away to clear a large area east of Sepulveda Blvd. in Westchester. The almost daily house-moving occurs east of northerly runways.

Title: Mayor Tom Bradley on podium with LAPD motorcycle drill team lined up before him during his inauguration in Los Angeles, Calif., 1973
Subject: African American mayors--California--Los Angeles
Caption: INAUGURAL CEREMONIES--At left, part of Los Angeles Police Department's motorcycle drill team lines up before Mayor Tom Bradley at reviewing stand.

Title: Mayor Tom Bradley speaking in city council chambers about proposed jobs cuts, panoramic, Los Angeles, Calif., 1978
Subject: African American mayors--California--Los Angeles
Caption: IN WAKE OF PROP. 13--Mayor Bradley addressing City Council on proposals to fire about 8,300 city employes [sic], including 1,080 policemen. Latter figure was suggested by police chief, Bradley said.

Title: CÃ©sar ChÃ¡vez, Paul Schrade and other strikers picketing Ford Motor Co. plant at Pico Rivera in Los Angeles, Calif., 1967
Subject: Strikes and lockouts--Automobile industry--California--Los Angeles
Caption: IN UAW PICKET LINE--Cesar Chavez , left, director of United Farm Workers Organizing Committee, leads some of his union members in picketing the Ford Motor Co. plant at Pico Rivera in support of striking United Auto Workers. With him is Paul Schrade, UAW western director who is directing the strikers.

Title: Los Angeles City Hall's cornerstone being lowered down to its place during ceremonies in 1927
Subject: City halls--Design and construction
Subject Name: Los Angeles City Hall (Los Angeles, Calif.)
Caption: In the photo below the corner-stone of the new City Hall is shown being seated at the exercises yesterday.

Title: Crowd observing the Feast of Corpus Christi in Los Angeles, Calif., 1940
Subject: Catholic Church--Liturgy
Caption: IN ANCIENT RITUAL: Section of the crowd of devout Catholics who yesterday observed the Feast of Corpus Christi shown as priest, with Holy Sacrament, pronounces the benediction.

Title: Los Angeles City Councilman Ed Davenport speaking during debate on requiring Communists to register, 1950
Subject: Communism--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: IN ACTION--Councilman Ed Davenport, who proposed anti-Communist ordinance.

Title: Father Fidel Zapatero conducting washing of the feet on Holy Thursday in Los Angeles, Calif., 1948
Subject: Catholic Church--Liturgy
Subject Name: Our Lady Queen of Angels Catholic Church (Los Angeles, Calif.)
Caption: IMPRESSIVE CEREMONY -- Holy Thursday was observed yesterday at the Church of Our Lady Queen of Angels with the traditional ceremony of the washing of the feet.  Father Fidel Zapatero presided at the services.

Title: Mrs. William Gude and daughter Wendy look through shattered window, 1950.
Subject: Mother and child--California, Southern
Caption: IMPERILED - In their home across the street from Mickey Cohen's house Mrs. William Gude and daughter Wendy look through a shattered window.  The little girl was showered with glass particles and frightened into hysterics when dynamite exploded.

Title: Aerial view of coastline and Marina del Rey, barren expect for a few docks, Calif., 1963
Subject: Coastlines--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: IMPACT-The magnificent Marina del Rey went into full-scale use during the past year. This air view shows scope of marina, with outlet at upper left. The marina carries significant effects for area.

Title: Collapsed scaffolding surrounding columns during construction of Simi Valley-San Fernando Valley Freeway, Calif., 1974
Subject: Windstorms--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: ILL WIND--Twisted scaffolding of ramp under construction on Simi Valley-San Fernando Valley Freeway after it was felled by strong winds.

Title: Archbishop of Los Angeles Archdiocese Roger Mahoney, 1986
Subject: Catholic Church--Bishops
Caption: I would think the hospice should serve victims of any faith or belief.' - Archbishop Roger Mahoney

Title: Dodgers' Steve Garvey leaping over Atlanta catcher Vic Correll to tag home base, Los Angeles, Calif., 1976
Subject: Baseball players--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HURDLING HOME--Steve Garvey (6) of Dodgers leaps over glove of Atlanta catcher Vic Correll to score tying run in seventh inning of first game of Sunday's doubleheader. However, the Braves scored in 10th inning for 3-2 win. Dodgers won the nightcap, 2-0.

Title: Daphne DiCino in her business executives room at Hyatt Regency in Los Angeles, Calif., 1977
Subject: Business travel--United States
Caption: HOTELS, AIRLINES FIND NEW BONANZA Hotels and travel-related firms discover a large market in the growing number of traveling businesswomen, such as, at downtown Hyatt Regency, public relations consultant Daphne DiCino of Phoenix takes advantage of work time in her room in hotel's new program for business executives--the Regency Club. Some rooms have special maids and butlers such as Vince Gonzales, shown preparing cocktails and hors d'oeuvre service while Ms. Mule works.

Title: Bing and Kathy Crosby on the terrace of the Del Monte Lodge, Pebble Beach during 29th annual Pro-Am Clambake, 1970
Subject: Golf--Tournaments--California--Pebble Beach
Caption: HOST AND HOSTESS-- Bing Crosby and his wife Kathy relax on the terrace of the Del Monte Lodge during Bing's 29th annual Pro-Am Clambake for golfers at Pebble Beach.

Title: Director Alfred Hitchcock receiving Producers Guild award from actors James Stewart and Cary Grant, 1965
Subject: Award presentations--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HONORED-Alfred Hitchcock, center, receives the Milestone Award from James Stewart, right, as Cary Grant looks on at Screen Producers Guild banquet.

Title: L.M. Giannini, president of Bank of America receives Financial Writers' Association Award, 1950.
Subject: Award presentations--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HONORED - L.M. Giannini, president of Bank of America, left, receives scroll from J.W. Ward, Financial Writers' president.

Title: President Gerald Ford on podium with running back Ricky Bell during campaign stop at University of Southern California, 1976
Subject: African American football players
Caption: HONORARY LETTERMAN--President Ford wears jacket just presented him by USC's running back Ricky Bell, applauding, during the president's midday appearance before USC student body.

Title: 11 year-old actress Margaret O'Brien seated on suitcase holding a doll at Los Angeles Union Station, 1948
Subject: Motion picture actors and actresses--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HOME AGAIN-- Margaret O'Brien, 11-year-old film star, returns to Southland from 22 days of travel abroad.  She holds a doll which was given her on visit to Paris.

Title: Crowd at Holy Name Union's ceremony in tribute to Our Lady of Guadalupe, Calif., 1940
Subject: Outdoor religious services--California--Los Angeles County
Subject Name: Mary, Blessed Virgin, Saint--Devotion to--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HOMAGE TO SAINT: Part of crowd at altar yesterday at Holy Name Union's ceremony in tribute to Our Lady of Guadalupe.

Title: Dodgers' Steve Garvey with wife Cyndy, and baby daughter, Krisha Lee in Los Angeles, Calif., 1974
Subject: Christmas trees
Caption: HOLIDAY MOOD--The Dodgers' Steve Garvey, National League MVP who was just named the Southern California Athletic of the Year by the Citizens Savings Athletic Foundation, celebrates the season with his wife, Cyndy, and daughter, Krisha Lee, who was born during World Series two months ago.

Title: Doug Flutie and Bob Hope carrying gymnast Mary Lou Retton during taping of Bob Hope's Christmas television show, 1984
Subject: Gymnasts--United States
Caption: Holiday horseplay--Heiseman Trophy winner Doug Flutie and Bob Hope hoist Olympic gymnastics champion Mary Lou Retton while taping Hope's Dec. 16 Christmas TV show.

Title: Agnes S. Albro, newly appointed police commissioner, inspects policewomen training in Los Angeles, Calif., 1946
Subject: Police recruits--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HITS THE DECK: Mrs. Curtis Albro, right, newly appointed Police Commissioner, saw demonstration of art of self-defense when she inspected new class of policewomen yesterday. Miss Audrey Melane uses combination of speed and skill to throw Sgt. George Danbacher, instructor, as other trainees study Audrey's technique.

Title: Bethune Junior High School students wearing ethnic African garb during Black History Week in Los Angeles, Calif., 1970
Subject: Junior high school students--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: HISTORY OBSERVANCE--Students at Bethune Junior High School, 155 W. 69th St., wear Afro style clothing Monday during observance of Afro-American Week, an outgrowth of Negro History Week. At left is Principal Norman Mathers, also wearing Afro garb. Special events of week include a Swahili lesson over the intercom, a fashion show, Afro dancing show, a soul food banquet and visits by celebrities.

Title: M. L. Calac, Indian bell ringer of Padua Mission, sounds old San Fernando Mission bell, 1946
Subject: Dedications--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: HISTORIC MOMENT: M. L. Calac, Indian bell ringer of Padua Mission, sounds old San Fernando Mission bell following dedication of restoration work on belfry.

Title: Los Angeles Costume Council watching a woman model costume from the movie "My Fair Lady," 1964
Subject: Women--California--Los Angeles--Societies and clubs
Subject Name: Los Angeles County Museum of Art. Costume Council
Caption: HIGH STYLE-On set of "My Fair Lady" are, from left, model Carol Mitchell, Mmes. Arthur L. Crowe Jr., Robert Hastings, Hughson Nerney of Costume Council.

Title: Los Angeles Ram's kicker Danny Villanueva in uniform doing the can-can with actress Susan Hart, 1964
Subject: Placekickers (Football);
Caption: HIGH KICKERS-Ram kicking specialist Danny Villanueva meets his match in leggy Susan Hart, co-star in Columbia's "Ride the Wild Surf," who appeared with Ram players during lively timeout at Chapman College in Orange.

Title: Los Angeles Police officer Carolyn L. Wallace being awarded the Medal of Valor, 1972
Subject: Award presentations--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HIGH HONOR--Policewoman Carolyn L. Wallace, first woman on the Los Angeles Police Department to be awarded Medal of Valor.

Title: Los Angeles Rams coach Chuck Knox on sideline during game in Los Angeles, Calif., 1973
Subject: Football coaches--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: HEY, REF!--Ram coach Chuck Knox yells to officials, claiming one of the Atlanta Falcons is holding on a play--and he tugs his own shirt for emphasis. The referee ignored the "help" from the sidelines and Knox needed no help in 31-0 win.

Title: American Airlines plane taxiing on overpass above Sepulveda Blvd. as automobile drives down street in Los Angeles, Calif., 1976
Subject: Airports--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: HEAVY TRAFFIC--Motorist who took a slightly wrong turn? Actually he has just topped a rise on Sepulveda Blvd. near L.A. Airport, and the plane is taxiing on an overpass in background. Foreshortening effect of telephoto lens accounts for the confusion.

Title: Dodgers' Fernando Valenzuela in wind up for pitch, Los Angeles, Calif., 1986
Subject: Baseball players--California--Los Angeles
Caption: Heaven Sent--Balloons and pitcher Fernando Valenzuela were in the ascendancy as the Dodgers opened the season at the Stadium with a 2-1 victory over San Diego Valenzuela scattered 10 hits and was the winning pitcher. Details in Sports.

Title: Pacific Colony nursery cribs jammed together due to overcrowding, 1950.
Subject: Memorials--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: HEAD TO FOOT - In the overcrowded nursery at Pacific Colony, the State hospital for mental defectives, infants are housed in cribs as shown above, so close that it is possible to reach into and adjoining crib.

Title: Kristen Commons, University Elementary School pupil, carries mortar on her head, 1958.
Subject: School children--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: HEAD CARRY â€“ Kristen Commons, University Elementary School pupil, carries mortar African style.

Title: General of the United States Army, Omar Nelson Bradley flanked by Peggy Stevenson and Tom Bradley in city council chambers Los Angeles, Calif., 1976
Subject: Award presentations--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HE'S NO. 1 in L.A.--General of the Army Omar Bradley, 83, receives from Councilwoman Peggy Stevenson and Mayor Tom Bradley the city's highest honor, a joint resolution from the City Council and mayor, in the council chambers. The general, wearing some of his 75 military decorations, will also receive the USO's first Distinguished American Award here on Wednesday.

Title: Artist Norman Rockwell standing amongst his paintings at exhibit at Municipal Art Gallery at Barnsdall Park, Calif., 1965
Subject: Painters--United States
Caption: HE PAINTS 'AMERICANA'-Artist Norman Rockwell stands beside painting, one of 23 he has on display at the Municipal Art Gallery at Barnsdall Park.

Subject: Neon signs
Caption: HAVEN FOR ALCOHOLICS-Glittering lights attract problem drinkers searching for a bar

Subject: Catholic universities and colleges--California--Los Angeles
Caption: HATS OFF!-Tipping freshman "dinks" to the statue of a lion symbolic of Loyola University are Mrs. John French, left, Mrs. Peter Vogelsang and Mrs. John Meichtry, among planners of Loyola alumni's fall dinner dance tonight.

Title: Dodger's manager Tommy Lasorda playing with shortstop, Dave Anderson's daughter, Christa, 1985
Subject: Baseball managers--California--Los Angeles
Caption: Hats off--Christa Anderson, the 13-month old daughter of the Dodgers' shortstop Dave Anderson, removes the hat of manager Tommy Lasorda Sunday at Dodger Stadium. USC defeated the Dodgers in an exhibition game, 6-5.

Title: Crowd viewing a 20-foot basking shark caught by fishermen in Long Beach, Calif., 1955
Subject: Basking shark
Caption: HARPOONED SEA GIANT-- huge basking shark which was harpooned and brought ashore at Pierpont Landing, Long Beach, by three fishermen.  The shark measures 20 feet 10 inches and weighs 2000 pounds.

Title: Congressman and labor union leaders in heated argument during Congressional committee inquiry into film strikes, Los Angeles, Calif., 1947
Subject: Confrontations
Caption: HARD WORDS -- Rep. Carroll D. Kearns, center, heading a Congressional committee inquiring into film strikes, tries to head off a fight as B.C. (Cappy) DuVal, right, business agent for Local 44 (property men of I.A.T.S.E.) bristles at the names he is being called by Herb Sorrell, left, president of striking Conference of Studio Unions.  DuVal has his hand on a hammer.  Clash occurred as Kearns visited M.G.M. studio to inspect conditions.

Title: Lt. General Kenneth W. Schultz with airspace model in anechoic chamber at Air Force Systems Command in El Segundo, Calif., 1973
Subject: Anechoic chambers
Subject Name: Los Angeles Air Force Station (Calif.)--Officials and employees
Caption: HAPPY COMBINATION--Space-age career and gracious living in Bel-Air are combined by Lt. Gen. and Mrs. Kenneth W. Schultz. The general, head of the Space and Missile Systems Organization, Air Force Systems Command at El Segundo, is looking at a model of a space vehicle or warhead in the base anechoic (no echo) chamber used to test microwave action under conditions simulating those of outer space.

Title: Los Angeles Lakers' Jerry West and other players signing autographs at fund raiser in Los Angeles, Calif., 1971
Subject: Fund raising--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: HANDS FULL--Eager fans crowd around as Jerry West signs autographs at the Lakers' free benefit workout Monday at the Forum. Money collected from fans will go to the families of the three Cal State Fullerton coaches killed in an air crash. An estimated $11,000 was raised at drill.

Title: Magic Johnson and Pat Riley riding on float during parade celebrating the Los Angeles Lakers' 1982 Championship
Subject: Victory celebrations--California--Los Angeles
Caption: Hailing the heroes--Thousands line Broadway and Magic Johnson waves from float as Los Angeles honors its world-champion Lakers with a parade. Coach Pat Riley stands behind Johnson, and mounted police control crowd. Lakers routed 76ers in six games.

Title: Akiko Tsukimoto, arriving with "Friendship Flame" from Japan meeting priest H. Araki in Los Angeles, Calif., 1939
Subject: Cultural relations
Caption: HAIL TO TRADITION: Miss Tsukimoto is met by kimono-clad girls and priest, H. Araki. The Flame, legend says, has been kept alive 1500 years.

Title: Boxer Muhammad Ali making way through crowd during retirement salute at the Forum in Inglewood, Calif., 1979
Subject: Retirement
Caption: HAIL TO THE CHAMP--Muhammad Ali gets a tumultuous reception Thursday at Forum salute.

Title: Clarence A. Dykstra, UCLA Provost, and first-grader Jeannie Morgan break ground for University Elementary School at UCLA, 1949.
Subject: School children--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: GROUND TURNED - Provost Clarence A. Dykstra and Jeannie Morgan, a first-grader, break ground for the first unit of the University Elementary School at UCLA.

Title: Mr. and Mrs. Lodge are greeted by Mr. and Mrs. Ronald Reagan prior to Lodge's Republican dinner in Los Angeles, Calif., 1960
Subject: Politicians--California--Los Angeles
Caption: GREETED-Mr. and Mrs. Lodge are greeted by Mr. and Mrs. Ronald Reagan prior to Lodge's Republican dinner address at the Sports Arena.  Mrs. Lodge is at left and Mrs. Reagan is next to her.  During speech Lodge called cold war important issue in 1960 campaign.

Title: Bob Hope embracing his daughter, Nora after her graduation from Providence High School in Burbank, Calif., 1964
Subject: High school graduates--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: GRADUATION-Bob Hope embraces his daughter, Nora, 17, after her graduation from Providence High School in Burbank. The comedian delivered the commencement address, which was full of the kind of humor that made his fortune.

Title: Bernice Brown, governor's wife, visiting Dennis the Menace Children's Park in Downey, Calif., 1966
Subject: Parks--California--Los Angeles County
Subject Name: California. Governor's Action Advisory Committee on California Beauty
Caption: GOVERNOR'S WIFE ON TOUR-Mrs. Edmund G. Brown tries to pull King Arthur's magic sword from its stone during visit to Dennis the Menace Children's Park in Downey. Mrs. Brown and members of the Governor's Action Advisory Committee on California Beauty are on four-day tour of community, individual and commercial beauty projects.

Title: Baseball Managers Fred Haney and Branch Rickey at Hollywood Stars baseball game, 1950
Subject: Baseball managers--California--Los Angeles
Caption: GOT HANEY HELP?--Star Manager Fred Haney huddles with Branch Rickey of Dodgers (left) yesterday at Gilmore Field. Conversation was about, of all things, baseball.

Title: Boy Scout wiping the eyes of girl during smog alert in Reseda, Calif., 1965
Subject: Air--Pollution--Physiological effect--California--Los Angeles
Caption: GOOD TURN ON BAD DAY-Jeffrey La France, a Reseda boy scout, helps Nancy Rayder, 11, dry her eyes during four-hour smog alert called in Reseda.

Title: D. D. McClurg announcing end of Pacific Electric strike in Los Angeles, Calif., 1946
Subject: Strikes and lockouts--Local transit--California--Los Angeles
Caption: GOOD NEWS: D. D. McClurg, head of transit workers union, announces that Los Angeles streetcar and bus strike is ended, after mass meeting accepted new plan.

Title: Joan A. Merriam Smith loading plane in preparation for solo around the world flight, Calif., 1964
Subject: Flights around the world
Caption: GOOD LUCK CHARM-Joan A. Merriam holds good luck teddy bear as she prepares for Oakland take off on her round-the-world 27,000-mile flight.

Title: Los Angeles Police Chief William H. Parker getting a kiss from his wife Helen, 1964
Subject: Police chiefs $z California $z Los Angeles
Caption: GOING TO INDIA-Police Chief William H. Parker gets kiss from wife, Helen, at International Airport as he boarded plane for Washington, first stop on his trip to India as a State Department expert on police affairs. Parker has been granted a six-month leave of absence to help the government of India strengthen its law enforcement administration.

Title: Comedian Peter Sellers sitting up in ambulance gurney with wife Britt Eklund in Los Angeles, Calif., 1964
Subject: Comedians--Great Britain
Caption: GOING HOME-British comedian Peter Sellers, 38, stricken with a heart attack April 6 that almost cost him his life, gets a hug from his Swedish actress wife, Britt Eklund, 21, as he leaves Cedars of Lebanon Hospital on an ambulance litter Thursday.

Title: Aerial view of drought-depleted Lake Shasta, Calif., 1976
Subject: Droughts--California--Shasta County
Caption: GOING DOWN--Low shoreline shows how Lake Shasta water levels have dropped since drought hit. View is of the marina near the dam.

Some officials of Thousand Oaks want the law barring annexation across county lines changed to permit them to incorporate all of the village, in two counties. Caption: ABOUT SMOG-Mrs. Afton Slade, president of SOS (Stamp Out Smog), at press conference at the Ambassador. In foreground is a special birthday cake celebrating smog's 21st anniversary.

Title: Mark Sato with his maze project that won a trophy at Science Fair at the California Museum of Science and Industry, 1970
Subject: Science museums--Educational aspects--California--Los Angeles County
Subject Name: California Museum of Science and Industry
Caption: A-MAZING RATS-- Mark Sato, 13, puts his rats through maze for project that won him a trophy at Science Fair at Museum of Science and Industry. Sato was one of 10 first-prize winners from junior and senior high schools. The exhibit of 325 science projects will continue daily through Sunday.

Title: Comedienne Phyllis Diller being awarded honorary house mother of Alpha Epsilon Pi Fraternity at UCLA, 1966
Subject: Fraternities & sororities--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: A WELCOME FOR 'MOM'-Comedienne Phyllis Diller is the center of attention as she becomes honorary house mother of Alpha Epsilon Pi Fraternity at UCLA. The president of the fraternity chapter, Lloyd Schwartz, right, prepares to present a plaque to the zany comedienne.

Title: Mount Wilson Observatory complex in Los Angeles, Calif., 1984
Subject: Observatories--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: A view from atop Mt. Wilson complex and from afar, below. Its telescopes are 65 to 80 years old.

Title: Los Angeles Junior League member, Elizabeth Bell, modeling evening gown designed by Galanos, 1955
Subject: evening dresses (garments)
Caption: A STUNNING BALL GOWN was worn, and well, by Mrs. Alphonzo E. Bell Jr., above. Designed by Galanos its full silken shirt duplicated the colors of the Italian flag.

Title: John Coffman, president of Committee for Rhodesian Independence in Support of Ian Smith, speaking to crowd at UCLA, 1967
Subject: Public speaking
Subject Name: Committee for Rhodesian Independence in Support of Ian Smith
Geographic Coverage: Zimbabwe--Politics and government--1965-1979--Foreign public opinion, American
Caption: A SPEECH THAT PRECEDED TROUBLE--John Coffman, president of Committee for Rhodesian Independence, speaks to crowd at UCLA before scheduled burning of Soviet, Nazi and U.N. flags.

Title: Man removing withered flowers before Marilyn Monroe's crypt in Westwood Memorial Park, Calif., 1975
Subject: Lifestyle
Caption: A SPECIAL REMEMBRANCE-- Floral delivery man removes withered flowers from area around Marilyn Monroe's crypt in Westwood Memorial Park after placing red roses from her second husband, Joe DiMaggio, in receptacle above. It was the 13th anniversary of the famed actress' death.

Title: Honolulu Avenue after the catastrophic January flood and mudslide, La Crescenta-Montrose, 1934
Subject: Landslides $z California $z La Crescenta-Montrose
Caption: A similar photograph appears with the caption: Raging Flood Leaves Mantle of Mud Over Streets and Yards in La Crescenta Area: Scenes in Wake of Disastrous Storm. Panorama of flood devastated area in the La Crescenta district, this view showing mud-covered Honolulu avenue in Montrose... [Los Angeles Times, 3 Jan. 1934: A1]

Title: Mayor-elect Tom Bradley shaking hands with supporters at mayoral victory celebration in Los Angeles, Calif., 1973
Subject: Victory celebrations--California--Los Angeles
Caption: A SEA OF HANDS--Mayor-elect Tom Bradley reaches out to greet his jubilant supporters at a victory celebration at the Los Angeles Hilton. Bradley defeated Mayor Sam Yorty in a landslide.

Title: Angels baseball manager Bill Rigney, flanked by Disneyland characters at groundbreaking ceremonies for Anaheim Stadium, 1964
Subject: Pluto (Fictitious character)
Caption: A RIG-GED PENNANT-Angel manager Bill Rigney, flanked by Disneyland characters, Pluto and Mickey Mouse, is presented a "pennant" at groundbreaking ceremonies for new stadium in Anaheim Monday. Angels will play in $16 million stadium starting in '66.

Title: Cityscape of downtown Los Angeles, viewed from Dodger Stadium, 1972
Subject: Landmarks
Caption: A RARE LOS ANGELES MORNING--Smog was nowhere to be seen this morning over downtown. Picture was taken from Dodger Stadium.

Title: Mayor Sam Yorty and engineer S.S. Taylor demonstrating radar speed meter in Los Angeles, Calif., 1972
Subject: Radar in speed limit enforcement--Equipment and supplies
Caption: A RADAR REMINDER--Mayor Sam Yorty and S.S. (Sam) Taylor, city traffic engineer, with a radar-activated meter that shows motorists how fast they are driving. Device, first of four planned, was demonstrated outside City Hall. It was conceived by Taylor for use in city's high-speed areas.

Title: Motorists lined up at gas station during oil crisis, Los Angeles, Calif., 1973
Subject: Automobiles--United States--1970-1980
Caption: A QUICK FILL-UP--Motorists trying to beat the threat of gasoline station closings line up in the street at station on N. Broadway in Los Angeles.

Title: Department of Children's Services nurse examining baby at MacLaren Hall in El Monte, Calif., 1984

Title: Filipino folk dancers performing tinikling dance on steps of Los Angeles City Hall, 1966
Subject: Filipino Americans--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: A JULY FOURTH QUICK-STEP-Filipino folk dancers entertain crowd at the City Hall with the Tinikling in which they step in and out of bamboo poles being slammed together at a rapid rhythm. The dance was part of the celebration of Philippine independence day, which also falls on the Fourth of July.

Title: Les Layton, Jess Dobernic and Gene Baker at home plate during Hollywood Stars vs Los Angeles Angels game, 1950
Subject: Baseball umpires--United States
Caption: A GOOD WELCOME HOME-- Les Layton, after socking three-run homer in ninth to ice opener for Los Angeles, is given welcome home by Jess Dobernic, left and Gene Baker, who scored also.  Umpire is Roman Bentz.

Title: Kirk Douglas smearing cement on Ken Murray's face at Grauman's Chinese Theater, 1962
Subject: Motion picture actors and actresses--Commemoration
Caption: A FRACAS IN CEMENT-Kirk Douglas gives Ken Murray a cement facial after putting his hand prints into concrete at Grauman's Chinese Theater.  Above the two, left to right, are James Harry Brown, Jackie Cooper and Mrs. Murray.  Also present was Donald O'Conner and Jeanne Crain, almost hidden by Douglas.

Title: Lifeguard and woman inspecting oil covered beach in Santa Monica, Calif., 1969
Subject: Seashore--California--Los Angeles County
Caption: A BLACK 'POX' ON THE BEACH--Beachgoer Roslyn Leone, 20, a student, and lifeguard Lt. Tom Johnson inspect patches of oil that have washed ashore at Santa Monica. The patches, which have appeared on beaches as far south as Laguna Beach, apparently are from the leaking Santa Barbara well. Union Oil Co., although not admitting responsibility, sent a crew to begin clearing the Santa Monica strand.

Subject: Outdoor recreation--California--Los Angeles County
